## 2026-04-03 - dtcg-resolver.ts loadSource silently swallows cycle and bad-reference errors
- Replaced `console.warn` in `loadSource` with a `ResolverDiagnostic[]` accumulator threaded through the call stack. Added `ResolverDiagnostic` (`{ severity, message }`) and `ResolverResult` (`{ tokens, diagnostics }`) types. Changed `resolveTokens` return type from `Promise<Record<string, Token>>` to `Promise<ResolverResult>`. Updated `resolveTokensFull` similarly. Updated `resolver-store.ts:resolve()` to return `Promise<ResolverResult>`. Updated the `/resolvers/:name/resolve` route to include `diagnostics` in the JSON response so callers can surface errors in the UI.
- Files changed: `packages/core/src/dtcg-resolver.ts` ~L124-141 (types), ~L154-211 (resolveTokens), ~L213-232 (resolveTokensFull), ~L265-310 (loadSource); `packages/core/src/index.ts` ~L129 (exports); `packages/server/src/services/resolver-store.ts` ~L12-16 (import), ~L172-196 (resolve); `packages/server/src/routes/resolvers.ts` ~L179-192 (route)
- **Learnings for future iterations:**

